s an assortment of workouts and features that will keep you busily strengthening muscle groups as you enhance your cardiovascular fitness.","Of this line, the LifeFitness X3 <a href=\"/best-elliptical-machines\">elliptical machine</a> comes with two different consoles: the Track Elliptical Console and the Go Elliptical Console. With the more advanced Track version, you can access 14 different preset workout programs that you can change to suit your exercise needs and overall health improvement goals.","You also get custom workouts, warm-up and cool-down modes, and a quick-start option for your elliptical workouts. You can store fitness data for up to four different users. Included in the workouts are options such as Fat Burn, Sport Training and Extreme Heart Rate. There is even an option titled EZ Resistance for a less intense workout session.","If you want to charge up your exercise sessions, you can choose from 16 different resistance levels. In addition, you can automatically change the incline to make your workouts more or less challenging, depending on what your fitness plan for that day is as well as your overall health improvement goals.","You can keep track of your heart rate by grasping hand sensors on the stationary handlebars of this elliptical or you can use the heart-rate monitoring chest strap.","If you opt for the Track elliptical console, you get iPod compatibility, which can make your exercise sessions considerably more enjoyable. In addition, this particular console offers access to the Life Fitness LFconnect app so you can make your own customer exercise sessions and keep records of your results online. You can use a USB port to connect the Life Fitness Virtual Trainer app on your mobile device to the console.","This is a good-sized elliptical machine that is 81 inches long, 30 inches wide and 59 inches high. It weighs 215 pounds and can handle workouts by people who are as heavy as 350 pounds. The flywheel weighs 26 pounds.","The warranties on this elliptical machines are good, but not overly generous. You get a lifetime warranty for the frame, a three-year warranty for parts and a one-year warranty for labor. If you have any difficulties, you can contact the company by phone or email, or you can make use of the online manual and the website&#39;s FAQs section."]},"id":"20e1f15d-eb81-4004-9233-5aaf21907a28","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Summary"},"id":"c725314c-21cb-4b4b-be65-2454cf4d8ab8","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["This LifeFitness X3 elliptical offers a choice of two consoles, a variety of workout programs and the chance to adjust them to suit your exercise needs."]},"id":"56986928-ca8e-41f1-839d-ee2ac37567eb","type":"text"}]],"body":null,"legacyId":"product_review_page_58401","url":"/lifefitness-x-review","authors":[{"email":"","slug":"jennifer-christensen","url":"/author/jennifer-christensen","dateCreated":"2019-04-12T16:48:24Z","name":"Jennifer Christensen","dateModified":"2019-04-12T16:48:24Z","id":"qX8C3ZuWD5WJi4xoRSY64e","dateImported":null,"site":"toptenreviews"}],"territories":["US","GB"],"companies":[],"dateCreated":"2013-12-10T21:13:09Z","datePublished":"2013-12-10T21:13:09Z","name":"LifeFitness X 3","synopsis":"Editor’s Note: This product has been removed from viewing as part of this site because it has been replaced by another product. You can still read our original review below, but Top Ten Reviews is no longer updating this product’s information.","review":{"rating":83,"verdict":"The LifeFitness X elliptical provides a choice between two programmable consoles and offers a variety of workout programs and features.","pros":["This elliptical machine can accommodate a workout by someone who weighs up to 350 pounds."],"cons":["The stride length is set at 20 inches."]},"strapline":"Editor’s Note: This product has been removed from viewing as part of this site because it has been replaced by another product. You can still read our original review below, but Top Ten Reviews is no l